                              Mission Statement
            _____________________________________________________

   SEPRL provides scientific solutions to national and international
   exotic and emerging poultry disease problems that impact poultry and
   human health. The comprehensive research program emphasizes basic and
   applied research in diagnostics, prevention and control strategies,
   prediction of disease outbreaks, molecular epidemiology, and
   understanding disease pathogenesis. Research programs serve the needs
   of the poultry industry, state and federal government regulatory
   agencies, and the consumer. The Center uses a multi-diciplinary
   approach utilizing state-of-the-art technology and specialized
   facilities to conduct basic and applied research.

   Current research programs are Avian Influenza, Newcastle Disease, Avian
   Pneumovirus, Salmonella enteritidis, Poult Enteritis Mortality
   Syndrome, Avian Mucosal Immunology, and Vaccines.
